; Resolve all packages through the Microsoft package-feed proxy instead of the
; public npm registry. It screens for supply-chain / 0-day-vulnerable packages
; before they enter the build. Mirror this in the global npm/pnpm registry on
; each machine (see the README "Development" section).
;
; NB: package.json pins pnpm@11.9.0 via `packageManager` (the base-image version),
; but the proxy can't serve pnpm's own tarball in the integrity-only form pnpm
; needs, so `pmOnFail: ignore` in pnpm-workspace.yaml makes pnpm use the installed
; pnpm instead of self-provisioning. (Only registry + auth are read from .npmrc.)
registry=https://packagefeedproxy.microsoft.io/npm/

; Don't let pnpm phone the registry for its own "update available?" version check
; (pnpm's update-notifier, ON by default). It's unnecessary and, against the
; metadata-only proxy above, that probe fails/stalls — the "pnpm reaches out"
; symptom on a locked-down host. `pmOnFail: ignore` (pnpm-workspace.yaml) already
; stops the separate packageManager self-provisioning; this covers the update check.
update-notifier=false
